cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.Medical Imaging, cs.NE 

The paper deals with semantic segmentation in medical imaging using deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses few-shot learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of surrogate tasks for feature learning suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on medical imaging suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.Medical Imaging. Finally, the use of deep neural networks suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
